Docker Workflow Breakdown
-> Image Management
- docker pull ubuntu → Fetches the Ubuntu image from Docker Hub.
- docker images → Lists all images you’ve downloaded locally.
- docker rmi ubuntu → Removes the Ubuntu image from your system.
-> Container Lifecycle
- docker run ubuntu → Creates and runs a container from the Ubuntu image.
- docker run -it ubuntu /bin/bash → Runs Ubuntu interactively with a terminal session.
- docker stop <container_id> → Stops a running container.
- docker rm <container_id> → Deletes a stopped container.
-> System Cleanup
- docker system prune -a → Removes unused containers, images, and networks.
- docker system prune -a --volumes → Removes everything above plus volumes (be careful—this wipes persistent data).

